s.\n\n#### Sustainability\n- Finally, it addresses modern shifts towards sustainable agriculture practices in Champagne.\n\n### Conclusion\nChampagne not only remains a key player in the world of sparkling wines due to its historical prominence and unique production standards, but also adapts to modern challenges such as climate and sustainability.\n\n### Image\n- There is an accompanying map showing the geographical layout of Champagne with its sub-regions and some key cities marked.\n\n### Table or Key for the Map\n- Explains the scale of the map with indications: 0-100 m, 100-200 m, and 200+ m (elevation).\n\nThis summary outlines the essential information given about Champagne, emphasizing its regulations, geographical delineation, viticultural practices, and shifts towards sustainability, crucial for understanding the context and significance of this famous wine-producing region."
