    "source": "the_and_sugar_a_of",
    "contenu": "## TOBY’S LIME CORDIAL\n\n### Instructions:\n1. **Preparation of Zest and Juice:**\n   - Strip the zest from 12 limes, reserving the zest.\n   - Juice the limes.\n   \n2. **Mixing:**\n   - Weigh the lime juice and use an equal amount of sugar.\n   - In a nonreactive container, combine the lime juice and sugar.\n   - Stir until the sugar is dissolved.\n   - Stir in the lime zest and adjust flavor and texture by adding more lime juice or sugar as needed.\n\n3. **Resting and Storage:**\n   - Let the mixture stand at room temperature for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.\n   - Strain through a fine-mesh sieve.\n   - Store in the refrigerator for up to 1 month.\n\n## TOBY’S SOUR CHERRY SHRUB\n\n### Instructions:\n1. **Preparation of Cherries:**\n   - Rinse 2 quarts of sour cherries and trim any rot.\n   - Put the cleaned cherries in a large nonreactive pot.\n   - Crush slightly using hands or a wooden spoon.\n\n2. **Mixing and Fermenting:**\n   - Cover the cherries with vinegar (preferably Bragg’s or similar).\n   - Let the mixture stand at room temperature for 1 week, stirring daily.\n   - Ignore any unpleasant smell or sludge forming on top.\n\n3. **Boiling:**\n   - After 1 week, add ½ cup of raw sugar and boil gently for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.\n\n4. **Straining and Testing:**\n   - Cool the mixture slightly.\n   - Strain through a cheesecloth-lined fine-mesh sieve.\n\n5. **Serving Preparation:**\n   - Make a test shrub: Pour 3 to 4 tablespoons of the cherry mixture into a 20-ounce glass filled with ice.\n   - Add water or club soda almost to the rim.\n   - Stir in the chilled cherry mixture and adjust the sweetness by adding more sugar if required.\n   - Stir until sugar is dissolved.\n\n6. **Final Adjustments and Storage:**\n   - Once the desired taste is achieved, cool the shrub completely.\n   - Store in the refrigerator, where it will keep indefinitely."
